						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1494 (1572 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Mentions Anamtayya, son of Nēbati Rāmayya and others and seems to refer to their visit to the temple. The details of the date viz. <hi rend="bold">Śaka 149[4], Āṅgīra[sa], Jyēshṭha, śu. 15, Monday correspond to 1572 A.D., May 26, f.d.t. ·48.</hi> (See No. 494 below.)</p>						

